fsm.short_desc: Qogs are no-code logic elements based on finite state machines; they can be used anywhere in Qorus as an alternative to coding

class.short_desc: Classes that can be used in Qorus interface code

group.short_desc: Interface groups allow interfaces to be enabled and disabled together as well as enabling views on interfaces to be restricted for certain users

job.short_desc: Jobs execute logic on a user-defined schedule

mapper.short_desc: Mappers are visual data transformation elements

mapper-code.short_desc: Mapper code elements are classes with methods that can be directly used in mappers for complex data transformation logic

pipeline.short_desc: Data pipelines enable large volumes of data to be processed efficiently

queue.short_desc: Asynchronous step queues connect the front end to the back end of asynchronous workflow steps

service.short_desc: Services are a top-level interfacing object in Qorus

step.short_desc: Steps are an atomic execution element in a workflow

value-map.short_desc: Value maps provide simple mappings from one value to another

workflow.short_desc: Workflows are the primary stateful orchestration interface type in Qorus
